In article &lt;8810211535.AA00182@ron.rutgers.edu&gt; ron@HARDEES.RUTGERS.EDU (Ron Natalie) writes:
&gt;We intend to use it.  Probably something like
&gt;
&gt;	IN	TXT	LOC=Room-12
&gt;
&gt;	IN	TXT	SERVER=BUTLER
&gt;
&gt;(although I may make them pairs rather than using equals).
&gt;
&gt;The only problem is the last version of BIND I put up has
&gt;not got TXT records in it.  I talked to Mike Karels about this
&gt;and it's just a matter of who gets around to putting the code
&gt;in first, it really should be there.f
&gt;
&gt;-Ron


MIT's Project Athena uses it for the Hesiod name service; indeed, TXT
was added because Hesiod required it.

A version of BIND 4.8 that includes TXT support (as well as the rest
of the Hesiod support) is available by anonymous ftp to athena-dist.mit.edu,
in pub/hesiod.tar.Z.  This file is also available on gatekeeper.dec.com.

For more information about Hesiod, send mail to hesiod-request@athena.mit.edu.

	Win Treese
	Digital Equipment Corp.
	Cambridge Research Lab &amp; MIT Project Athena
	treese@athena.mit.edu, treese@crl.dec.com

